Class ClackData

  • java.lang.Object
    • data.ClackData
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FileClackData, MessageClackData

    public abstract class ClackData
extends java.lang.Object
    This is a superclass that represents the data sent between the client and the server.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ClackData

        public ClackData(java.lang.String userName,
                 int type)
        Constructor creates an instance of ClackData based on user-provided username and type. The date is automatically recorded. Based on the type will create an object of MessageClackData or FileClackData
        Parameters:
        userName - The client's username
        type - The current type

      • ClackData

        public ClackData(int type)
        Constructor that creates an anonymous user ("Anon") with a user-provided type. The date is automatically recorded.
        Parameters:
        type - The type

      • ClackData

        public ClackData()
        Default constructor creates an anonymous user ("Anon") with invalid type to show something went wrong. The default constructor should not be used if everything is working. The date is automatically recorded.
